sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS model_count
FROM model_sharing
WHERE user_id = 0;

SELECT AVG(test_accuracy) AS average_test_accuracy
FROM model_evaluations
WHERE dataset_id = 1 AND feature_set_id = 1;

SELECT AVG(valid_accuracy) AS average_valid_accuracy
FROM model_evaluations
WHERE feature_set_id = 1 AND dataset_id = 0;

external_knowledge:
Multiple evaluations refer to cases where a model has been evaluated more than once on the same dataset and context set, allowing for a more robust assessment of its performance.; 
Validation accuracy is a measure of how well a model performs on a specific dataset.; 
In this context, 'Specific Dataset Name' and 'Specific Context Set Name' refer to specific pre-defined dataset and context set names.

